# 📘 COMPLETE GIT & GITHUB DOCUMENT (BEGINNER → REAL WORLD)

---

# 🧠 1. WHAT IS GIT & GITHUB

```text
Git      = Version control system (tracks code locally)
GitHub   = Cloud platform (stores code remotely)
```

---

## 🔄 COMPLETE FLOW

```text
Your Code → Git (local save) → GitHub (online storage)
```

---

# 🧩 2. GIT INTERNAL WORKING (VERY IMPORTANT)

```text
Working Directory → Staging Area → Local Repo → Remote Repo
```

| Stage      | Command      | What it does |
| ---------- | ------------ | ------------ |
| Working    | Edit files   | Your code    |
| Staging    | `git add`    | Select files |
| Local Repo | `git commit` | Save version |
| Remote     | `git push`   | Upload       |

---

# 🚀 3. FIRST TIME PROJECT SETUP

---

## ✅ Step 1: Create project

```bash
mkdir my-project
cd my-project
touch app.py
```

---

## ✅ Step 2: Initialize Git

```bash
git init
```

### 🧠 What it does:

* Creates `.git`
* Starts tracking

---

## ❌ Error: not a git repository

### WHY:

No `.git` folder

### FIX:

```bash
git init
```

---

## ✅ Step 3: Add files

```bash
git add .
```

### 🧠 What it does:

Moves files → staging

---

## ✅ Step 4: Commit

```bash
git commit -m "first commit"
```

### 🧠 What it does:

Creates snapshot of code

---

# 🌐 4. CONNECT TO GITHUB

---

## ✅ Create repo on GitHub

Example:

```text
https://github.com/chandanasr1745-cell/my-project
```

---

## ✅ Add remote

```bash
git remote add origin <repo-link>
```

### 🧠 What it does:

Links local → GitHub

---

## ❌ Error: remote already exists

### WHY:

Already connected

### FIX:

```bash
git remote set-url origin <new-link>
```

---

# 🚀 5. PUSH CODE

---

## ✅ First push

```bash
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
```

---

## ❌ Error: no upstream branch

### WHY:

Branch not linked

### FIX:

```bash
git push --set-upstream origin master
```

---

## 🧠 What `-u` does

```text
Creates connection:
local branch ↔ remote branch
```

---

## ❌ Error: authentication failed

### WHY:

GitHub removed password

### FIX:

Use **TOKEN**

---

## ❌ Error: rejected (fetch first)

### WHY:

Remote has code

### FIX:

```bash
git pull origin main --allow-unrelated-histories
git push
```

---

# 📥 6. PULL CODE

---

## ✅ Command

```bash
git pull origin main
```

---

## 🧠 What it does

```text
git pull = fetch + merge
```

---

## 🔄 Flow

```text
GitHub → download → merge → local updated
```

---

# 🔁 7. DAILY WORKFLOW

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "update"
git push
```

---

## Always before push:

```bash
git pull
```

---

# 🌿 8. BRANCHING (MOST IMPORTANT)

---

## 🧠 What is branch?

```text
Separate workspace for development
```

---

## ✅ Create branch

```bash
git checkout -b featureupdate
```

---

## 🧠 Breakdown

* `checkout` → switch
* `-b` → create branch
* `featureupdate` → branch name

---

## ✅ Push branch

```bash
git push -u origin featureupdate
```

---

## 🧠 What it does

```text
Creates remote branch + links it
```

---

## 🔄 Merge branch

```bash
git checkout main
git merge featureupdate
git push
```

---

